%
( XYZAC BACKPLOT + BREADCRUMB VALIDATION TEST )
( Purpose: verify path plotting and live tracer behavior for XYZ, A, C, and combined moves )
( Expected: )
(  1 XYZ-only moves produce normal connected breadcrumbs overlaid on plotted path )
(  2 A-only moves C fixed produce rotary arc behavior around A pivot, not machine Z0 )
(  3 C-only moves while A is tilted follow the tilted frame C rides on A )
(  4 Program-loaded backplot shows A/C programmed motion, not only XYZ )

( Safety / setup assumptions for sim: )
(  - Inch mode, G54 active )
(  - No cutter comp, no tool length comp )
(  - Motions are conservative and air-cut style )

G20 G17 G40 G49 G80 G90
G54
M6 T8 G43 H8

F200.0

( --- Phase 0: Known start --- )
G0 X0.000 Y0.000 Z1.000 A0.000 C0.000

( --- Phase 1: XYZ-only tracing baseline --- )
G1 Z0.500
G1 X1.500 Y0.000
G1 X1.500 Y1.500
G1 X0.000 Y1.500
G1 X0.000 Y0.000

( --- Phase 2: A-only motion at fixed XYZ --- )
( Breadcrumb should show rotary effect about A pivot location )
G0 X1.000 Y0.500 Z0.500 C0.000
F3600.00
G1 A20.000
G1 A40.000
G1 A20.000
G1 A0.000

( --- Phase 3: C-only motion with A tilted --- )
( C should rotate in A-tilted frame; breadcrumbs should follow tilted orientation )
G1 A30.000
G1 C90.000
G1 C180.000
G1 C270.000
G1 C360.000
G1 C0.000

( --- Phase 4: Combined XYZ + AC moves --- )
( Should produce continuous connected trace that overlays plotted transformed path )
G1 X2.000 Y0.500 A30.000 C45.000
G1 X2.500 Y1.000 A15.000 C120.000
G1 X2.000 Y1.500 A0.000 C180.000
G1 X1.500 Y1.000 A-15.000 C270.000
G1 X1.000 Y0.500 A0.000 C360.000

( --- Phase 5: Return / cleanup --- )
G0 Z1.500
G0 X0.000 Y0.000 A0.000 C0.000
M2
%